records.addlTxt:
Defendant Michael D Stone in court with attorney Manuel R. Galang.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
As to Count 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction with Huber release for medical care/treatment, Consecutive with Count 2 and any other time being served, with credit for 4 days served. 

As to Count 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 45 DAYS in the House of Correction with Huber release for medical care/treatment, Consecutive with Count 1 and any other time being served, with credit for 0 days served. 

As to both counts:  The Court STAYED these sentences and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 15 MONTHS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*If deemed necessary/appropriate by agent defendant to obtain mental assessment and if necessary, successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Take all prescription medication only in the manner/dosage as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No violent contact with victim Jeff M. or Betty A.;
*Participate in Anger Management program;
*Pay all supervision fees;

The Court orders the defendant to pay : As to Count 1: $300.00 fine.  As to Counts 1 and 2: all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of supervision period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment-bail to apply.  The Court orders the balance of bail, if any, to be held until issue of restitution resolved.  State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  Defense disputes restitution request; hearing date selected with the parties.  Appeal rights given. 
Filed;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
-Crime Victim Impact Statement.

Case scheduled for Restitution Hearing on 10-02-14 at 1:30 p.m. before Branch 21.
